message.content: cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.COMM, cs.SY - This paper deals with the design and analysis of a Random Access congestion control technique for interactive satellite terminals in the context of DVB standards. This involves aspects related to network protocols, information theory, communication systems, and system control. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.COMM (Communication and Networking), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
